// Triết-in-Triết IR lowerer port — bootstrap source for the
// self-hosting compiler ([ADR-0019][adr-0019] §A7.8 v0.7.8 umbrella).
//
// v0.7.8.1 — IR types + Instruction enum scaffolding. Mirrors
// crates/triet-ir/src/{types.rs, constant.rs, instr.rs, module.rs}:
// declares the SSA value / block / function / constant ID wrappers,
// the recursive `TypeTag` (via arena because Triết enum variants
// can't recursively contain themselves), the `Constant` value
// enum, the `Operand` union, the full 53-variant `Instruction`
// enum, the `BuiltinName` enum, and the `BasicBlock` / `Function`
// / `IrModule` / `IrProgram` containers. v0.7.8.{2..5} build the
// `lower_program` driver, the wire-format `read_program` /
// `write_program`, and the `lowerer_differential` byte-diff gate
// on top of this surface.
//
// Types coverage:
//   - 4 ID wrappers (`ValueId` / `BlockId` / `FuncId` / `ConstId`),
//     each carrying a `raw: Integer` payload + `*_display` helper
//     that reproduces Rust's `impl Display` (`%n` / `bn` / `@fn` /
//     `cn`).
//   - `TypeTag` (12 variants — Trit / Tryte / Integer / Long /
//     Trilean / String / Unit / Nullable / Vector / HashMap /
//     Outcome). Recursive references go through `TypeArena` (same
//     pattern as parser.tri / typecheck.tri).
//   - `Constant` (8 variants — Trit / Tryte / Integer / Long /
//     Trilean / String / Unit / Null) + `ConstantPool` (Vector +
//     identity-string index map for dedup).
//   - `Operand` 2-variant union (ValueOp / ConstOp).
//   - `Instruction` — 53 variants covering ADR-0007's full opcode
//     set: Const, 7 arithmetic, 5 Ł3 logic, 3 K3 logic, 6
//     comparisons, 5 conversions, 3 struct ops, 3 enum ops, 3
//     nullable ops, 4 call ops, 2 closure ops, 5 control-flow
//     terminators, Phi, 6 Outcome ops.
//   - `BuiltinName` (~24 variants — io / text / vector / hashmap /
//     string / path / fs / parse / assert).
//   - `PhiIncoming` carrier struct.
//   - `BasicBlock { id, name, instructions }`,
//     `Function { id, name, parameters, return_type, blocks }`,
//     `IrModule { path_segments, functions }`,
//     `IrProgram { modules, constants, witness_tables }`.
//
// v0.7.8.1 is types-only: no `lower_*` driver yet. Smoke main
// exercises construction + display of every Instruction variant +
// the IR program containers so the integration test
// (`ir_lowerer_types_smoke.rs`) can confirm the surface compiles +
// round-trips through the VM. v0.7.8.{2..5} build the actual
// lowerer logic on this foundation.
//
// [adr-0019]: ../docs/decisions/0019-self-hosting-compiler-bootstrap.md

module parser;

